$\Leftrightarrow \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n(n+1)} x^{n+1}=(1-x) \ln (1-x)+x$ 을 양변 적분하면
$$\begin{aligned}
& \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n(n+1)(n+2)} x^{n+2} \\
